lection of an\nappropriate set of base functions is also key. Conclusions. Temperature in the\nmid-atmosphere can be suitably characterized by IR spectroscopy with a\nresolution of at least 1000 (ideally ~2500). Obtaining the necessary S/N could\nbe feasible with future missions, such as the Origins Space Telescope or the\nLarge Interferometer for Exoplanets. Meanwhile a least squares fitting with\nappropriate base functions is also applicable for other classes of planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Dec 2019 09:07:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-23"}
