e (Tc) in the coexistence region decreases as a\nfunction of the distance to the zero temperature classical bicritical point.\nThis indicates that at the fine tuned value of this transition, the system\nattains the highest Tc in the region of coexistence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Dec 2019 13:51:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Dec 2019 12:37:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-11"}
