cond, the deduced\ntwist profiles in MCs range quasi-continuously from nearly uniform, to\nincreasing away from the FR axis, up to a reversal near the MC boundaries.\nThere is no trace of outsider cases, but a continuum of cases. Finally, the\nimpact parameter of the remaining FR crossed at 1 au is revised. Its\ndistribution is compatible with weakly flatten FR cross-sections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Dec 2019 14:06:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-23"}
